Title: Détective
Writer: Alain Sarde (screenplay), Philippe Setbon (screenplay), Jean-Luc Godard (adaptation), Alain Sarde (adaptation), Anne-Marie Miéville (adaptation), Philippe Setbon (adaptation), Alain Sarde (dialogue), Philippe Setbon (dialogue), Anne-Marie Miéville (dialogue)
Actors: Laurent Terzieff, Aurelle Doazan, Jean-Pierre Léaud, Nathalie Baye
Plot: In a palace of Paris. Two detectives are investigating a two-year-old murder. Emile and Francoise Chenal are putting pressure on Jim Fox Warner, a boxing manager, who owes them a huge amount of money. But Jim also owes money to the Mafia, and it seems the boxing match he is counting on to bail out will not be sufficient...
